        "items": [
          {
            "icon": "Star",
            "title": {
              "zh": "Understanding Your Design Vision",
              "en": "Understanding Your Design Vision"
            },
            "description": {
              "zh": "Every successful garment starts with a clear understanding of the brand’s vision. At Kellogg Fashion\n, we carefully review your sketches, reference images, measurements, fabric requirements, and construction details before creating the tech pack. Our team communicates closely with clients to confirm oversized fit proportions, garment weight, sewing details, printing placement, washing effects, and overall streetwear aesthetics. This process helps reduce misunderstandings and ensures your product is production-ready from the beginning.",
              "en": "Every successful garment starts with a clear understanding of the brand’s vision. At Kellogg Fashion\n, we carefully review your sketches, reference images, measurements, fabric requirements, and construction details before creating the tech pack. Our team communicates closely with clients to confirm oversized fit proportions, garment weight, sewing details, printing placement, washing effects, and overall streetwear aesthetics. This process helps reduce misunderstandings and ensures your product is production-ready from the beginning."
            }
          },
          {
            "icon": "Star",
            "title": {
              "zh": "Creating Accurate Technical Specifications",
              "en": "Creating Accurate Technical Specifications"
            },
            "description": {
              "zh": "Once the design direction is confirmed, our development team builds a detailed tech pack with precise garment specifications. This includes measurements, size grading, stitching methods, fabric composition, GSM details, trim information, label placement, print dimensions, and sewing construction. For heavyweight hoodies and oversized streetwear garments, we also include important production details such as rib width, shoulder drop measurements, hood construction, and shrinkage tolerance to ensure consistency during bulk production.",
              "en": "Once the design direction is confirmed, our development team builds a detailed tech pack with precise garment specifications. This includes measurements, size grading, stitching methods, fabric composition, GSM details, trim information, label placement, print dimensions, and sewing construction. For heavyweight hoodies and oversized streetwear garments, we also include important production details such as rib width, shoulder drop measurements, hood construction, and shrinkage tolerance to ensure consistency during bulk production."
            }
          },
          {
            "icon": "Star",
            "title": {
              "zh": "Fabric & Construction Confirmation",
              "en": "Fabric & Construction Confirmation"
            },
            "description": {
              "zh": "Before sampling begins, we confirm all material and construction details with the client. Our team helps recommend suitable fabrics such as French terry, brushed fleece, heavyweight cotton jersey, or garment-dyed materials based on the desired hand-feel and fit. We also review printing techniques, embroidery methods, washing processes, and sewing construction to ensure the tech pack matches real production capabilities. This stage is important for avoiding production delays and maintaining product quality.",
              "en": "Before sampling begins, we confirm all material and construction details with the client. Our team helps recommend suitable fabrics such as French terry, brushed fleece, heavyweight cotton jersey, or garment-dyed materials based on the desired hand-feel and fit. We also review printing techniques, embroidery methods, washing processes, and sewing construction to ensure the tech pack matches real production capabilities. This stage is important for avoiding production delays and maintaining product quality."
            }
          },
          {
            "icon": "Star",
            "title": {
              "zh": "Sampling, Revisions & Production Preparation",
              "en": "Sampling, Revisions & Production Preparation"
            },
            "description": {
              "zh": "After the tech pack is finalized, we move into sample development and production preparation. During sampling, our team checks fit accuracy, sewing quality, fabric performance, and wash results against the original tech pack specifications. Any revisions are updated directly into the tech pack to create a clear production standard for bulk manufacturing. This process allows Kellogg Fashion to deliver stable quality, consistent sizing, and efficient production for global streetwear brands.",
              "en": "After the tech pack is finalized, we move into sample development and production preparation. During sampling, our team checks fit accuracy, sewing quality, fabric performance, and wash results against the original tech pack specifications. Any revisions are updated directly into the tech pack to create a clear production standard for bulk manufacturing. This process allows Kellogg Fashion to deliver stable quality, consistent sizing, and efficient production for global streetwear brands."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
